Yojna Setu v4.0 — Unified 10-Agent AI System Master Blueprint
This document compiles the entire system specification, including the High-Level Design (HLD), Product Requirements Document (PRD), System Requirements Specification (SRS), Security Design Document, API Contract, and developer guidelines (CLAUDE.md) into a single source of truth for the v4.0 10-Agent decoupled GovTech architecture.

DOC 01 — Master Project Document
Version 4.0 — 10-Agent AI System
1. Executive Summary
Yojna Setu v4.0 is a production-grade, multi-agent conversational platform designed to connect Indian citizens with 419+ indexed Central and State social welfare schemes. Under v4.0, the platform transitions to a stateful 10-agent AI system built on LangGraph StateGraph to handle the citizen's entire lifecycle dynamically. The system enables accessibility via low-latency voice streams in 22 regional Indian languages and integrates WhatsApp notifications while strictly complying with the Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act of 2023.   

2. Problem Statement
Welfare delivery in India faces significant digital divide barriers:   

Linguistic Fragmentation: 22% of citizens speak languages outside the primary languages supported by traditional portals.   

Digital Exclusion: Illiterate or non-digitally literate populations cannot type complex search queries or navigate form-heavy government layouts.   

Complex Eligibility Rules: Welfare eligibility relies on multidimensional variables (caste, land, income, region, occupation) that are difficult for citizens to assess manually.   

Trust and Grievances: Citizens face application blockages on government sites without transparent status feedback or reachable dispute channels.   

3. System Architecture Summary
Yojna Setu v4.0 is a 10-agent AI system built on LangGraph StateGraph. A central Orchestrator Agent receives all citizen input (text, voice, WhatsApp) and routes to specialist agents based on intent. Agents 1-3 handle the core citizen journey (eligibility, scheme discovery, application guidance). Agents 4-9 handle advanced capabilities (document verification, grievance filing, proactive nudging, financial planning, scheme comparison, CSC field verification). Agent 10 is admin-facing (analytics and insights). All agents share a common state object (citizen profile + session history) and communicate via LangGraph message passing — not direct API calls between agents.   

