5. Core Capabilities
10-Agent AI System: LangGraph-orchestrated multi-agent architecture handles the complete citizen journey from scheme discovery to grievance resolution autonomously.   

Eligibility Reasoning (Agent 1): Self-directed ReAct loop decides its own tool call sequence to verify eligibility across income, category, state, occupation, disability, and land criteria.   

Autonomous Scheme Discovery (Agent 2): Persistent agent monitors PIB RSS, MyScheme, and 5 state portals. New Central schemes appear within 60 minutes of PIB announcement. Self-healing on source failures.   

Application Guidance (Agent 3): Autonomously navigates government portals via browser-use, pre-fills forms from citizen profile, generates step-by-step screenshot checklist.   

Document Verification (Agent 4): Verifies document authenticity, cross-checks fields against profile, detects expiry, confirms sufficiency per scheme requirements.   

Grievance Filing (Agent 5): Checks application status on govt portal, drafts grievance letter, submits to pgportal.gov.in, tracks resolution.   

Proactive Nudging (Agent 6): Background agent sends personalised WhatsApp alerts for upcoming deadlines, unapplied eligible schemes, missing documents.   

Financial Planning (Agent 7): Calculates total annual benefit across all eligible schemes, generates payment calendar, prioritises by application effort vs benefit value.   

Scheme Comparison (Agent 8): Side-by-side comparison of similar schemes, recommends correct one with plain-language reasoning in citizen's language.   

CSC Field Verification (Agent 9): Guides operators on alternative acceptable documents, generates pre-filled self-declaration forms for document-less citizens.   

Analytics and Insights (Agent 10): Admin-facing weekly report on drop-off rates, scheme confusion signals, state coverage gaps.   

Real-Time Voice (Pipecat + Sarvam): All agents accessible via voice in 22 Indian languages through the Orchestrator.   

