FR-9.1: Agent 6 shall run daily background check for citizens with upcoming scheme deadlines (7 days and 1 day prior).   

FR-9.2: Agent 6 shall run weekly new-scheme eligibility check for all active citizens.   

FR-9.3: Agent 6 shall not send more than 2 WhatsApp messages per citizen per week to avoid spam.   

FR-9.4: Agent 6 shall allow citizens to opt out of nudges via WhatsApp reply 'STOP'. Updates nudge_opted_out flag in citizen_profiles.   

FR-10: Agent 7 — Financial Planning
FR-10.1: Agent 7 shall calculate total annual benefit across all schemes citizen is eligible for. Output: {total_annual_benefit: number, breakdown: [{scheme, amount, frequency}]}.   

FR-10.2: Agent 7 shall generate a month-by-month payment calendar for all eligible schemes.   

FR-10.3: Agent 7 shall rank schemes by benefit-to-effort ratio based on payment values and complex application steps.   

FR-11: Agent 8 — Scheme Comparison
FR-11.1: Agent 8 shall accept two scheme IDs and return a structured comparison: eligibility discrepancies, benefit details, processes, and a clear recommendation.   

FR-11.2: Agent 8 shall detect when citizen query implies confusion between two similar schemes and invoke automatically.   

FR-11.3: Agent 8 shall return comparison in citizen's detected language.   

FR-12: Agent 9 — CSC Field Verification
FR-12.1: Agent 9 shall return list of acceptable alternative documents per scheme when primary document unavailable.   

FR-12.2: Agent 9 shall generate pre-filled self-declaration PDF using citizen profile fields.   

FR-12.3: Agent 9 shall return state-specific self-declaration validity rules.   

FR-13: Agent 10 — Analytics
FR-13.1: Agent 10 shall compute scheme drop-off rate: schemes shown vs saved vs application started.   

