2. Voice Pipeline Architecture
Real-time streaming is handled natively by FastAPI via the Pipecat pipeline framework, routing through Sarvam Saaras V3 for low-latency speech-to-text, Gemini 2.5 Flash for conversational logic, and Sarvam Bulbul V3 for natural-sounding audio synthesis. To prevent resource exhaustion, all voice interactions bypass the Spring Boot gateway entirely.   

3. Storage Definitions
MongoDB contains five transactional indexes with automatic indexing configurations:   

users: Tracks basic registration schemas.   

citizen_profiles: Encrypts sensitive demographic inputs (AES-256 Fernet).   

schemes: Machine-readable program parameters and embeddings.   

applications: Captures tracking histories.   

conversation_sessions: Logs conversation transcripts with a 90-day TTL.   

4. Multi-Agent System Architecture (LangGraph)
The core AI system is a LangGraph StateGraph with one Orchestrator and 10 specialist agents. All agents share a common GraphState object passed through the graph. Agents communicate via LangGraph message passing — never direct API calls between agents.   

