4.3 Agent Flows
Agent 1 — Eligibility Agent (LangGraph ReAct loop)
Tool Registry (6 tools):

get_profile_field(field) — fetches from shared GraphState profile.   

check_scheme_eligibility(scheme_id, profile) — hard rule check, returns pass/fail per criterion.   

verify_income_dbt(citizen_id) — cross-checks declared income against DBT transfer records.   

check_disability_registry(aadhaar_hash) — verifies disability certificate against UDID registry.   

fetch_state_rules(state, scheme_id) — fetches state-specific overrides for Central schemes.   

query_similar_outcomes(profile_hash) — finds anonymised outcomes of citizens with similar profiles.   

ReAct loop: Agent 1 reasons in natural language about which tool to call next. Example autonomous reasoning chain: "Citizen declared income ₹1.8L. Before confirming PM-KISAN eligibility I should verify_income_dbt to cross-check. DBT shows ₹2.1L transfers — above PM-KISAN threshold. Mark ineligible. Now check state-specific override for UP — UP has extended threshold to ₹2.5L. Citizen is eligible under UP override."   

Agent 2 — Discovery Agent (persistent event loop)
Runs as an always-on Cloud Run service (not a job) with its own LangGraph loop:
TRIGGER (PIB RSS new item OR daily cron) → fetch_source node (PIB text / MyScheme page / state portal) → gemini_extract node (structured eligibility_rules JSON) → deduplication_check node (scheme_code hash lookup in MongoDB) → upsert_node (insert new / update changed / skip identical) → embed_node (Atlas Vector Search, only changed schemes) → alert_node (notify admin of new schemes added today).   

Self-healing: If MyScheme returns 429 or blocks the crawler, Agent 2 switches to a sitemap fallback, logs the blockage in the admin_alerts collection, and backs off for 2 hours.   

Agent 3 — Application Guidance Agent (browser-use)
Domain whitelist (hardcoded, never changeable at runtime): *.gov.in domains only, pgportal.gov.in, scholarships.gov.in, pmayg.nic.in, pmkisan.gov.in.   

Flow:
TRIGGER (citizen selects scheme to apply) → portal_navigator (browser-use opens scheme apply URL) → form_analyser (identifies all form fields on current page) → profile_mapper (maps form fields to citizen_profiles fields) → pre_filler (fills mapped fields via browser-use) → screenshot_capturer (captures each completed step) → checklist_generator (Gemini generates step-by-step guide from screenshots) → missing_docs_detector (compares required fields vs profile — flags gaps) → output: {checklist, screenshots[], missing_docs[], pre_filled_count}.   

Agent 4 — Document Verification Agent
Extends the existing OCR pipeline. Once OCR extracts text:
document_classifier (income_cert | caste_cert | aadhaar | disability_cert | land_record) → date_extractor (issue_date, expiry_date, validity_period) → expiry_checker (flag if expired or expiring < 30 days) → profile_crosscheck (name, DOB, address vs citizen_profiles) → scheme_sufficiency_check (for each target scheme: is this doc type + validity sufficient?) → output: {doc_type, is_valid, mismatches[], insufficient_for_schemes[], expires_in_days}.   

Agent 5 — Grievance Agent (browser-use)
Domain Whitelist: pgportal.gov.in only.   

Flow:
status_checker (browser-use: opens scheme portal, finds application by externalAppId, returns status) → grievance_drafter (Gemini: drafts letter in citizen's language, correct ministry officer, correct format) → pgportal_submitter (browser-use: navigates pgportal.gov.in, fills grievance form, submits) → reference_storer (saves reference number to applications.grievance_ref) → output: {current_status, grievance_submitted, reference_number}.   

Agent 6 — Proactive Nudge Agent (scheduled)
Runs on dual triggers (daily cron for deadlines and weekly cron for new schemes):   

DAILY: deadline_scanner (schemes with application_deadline within 7 days OR 1 day) → eligible_citizen_finder (citizens matching scheme eligibility who haven't applied) → rate_limiter (max 2 messages/citizen/week, skip opted-out citizens) → whatsapp_sender (Twilio: personalised message in citizen's lang).   

WEEKLY: new_scheme_fetcher (schemes added in last 7 days) → profile_matcher (which existing citizens newly qualify) → rate_limiter → whatsapp_sender.   

Agent 7 — Financial Planning Agent
Flow: eligible_scheme_loader (all schemes where eligibility_score > 70) → benefit_calculator (sum annual benefit_amount per scheme) → payment_calendar_builder (month: [scheme, amount] based on scheme disbursement schedule) → effort_ranker (rank by benefit_amount / application_complexity_score) → output: {total_annual_benefit, breakdown[], calendar{}, ranked_by_effort[]}.   

Agent 8 — Scheme Comparison Agent
Flow: scheme_fetcher (loads full scheme docs for both scheme IDs) → eligibility_diff (compares eligibility_rules field by field) → benefit_diff (compares benefit_amount, benefit_type, frequency) → process_diff (compares application steps, documents required, portal difficulty) → profile_matcher (which scheme fits THIS citizen better and why) → localiser (outputs comparison in citizen's detected language) → output: {scheme_a, scheme_b, diffs{}, recommendation, reasoning}.   

Agent 9 — CSC Field Verification Agent
Flow: alternative_doc_finder (scheme_id + missing_doc_type → acceptable_alternatives[]) → self_declaration_validator (state_code → valid self-declaration formats[]) → form_generator (citizen profile + scheme_id → pre-filled self-declaration PDF) → output: {alternatives[], valid_formats[], pdf_blob}.   

Agent 10 — Analytics Agent (weekly scheduled)
Flow: dropoff_analyser (schemes shown vs saved vs applied — MongoDB aggregation) → confusion_detector (sessions with repeated questions on same criterion) → state_gap_finder (citizen state distribution vs scheme state coverage) → benefit_calculator (total estimated benefits unlocked this week) → report_generator (Gemini: narrative weekly report from aggregation data) → report_storer (admin_reports collection) → output: stored weekly report + admin WhatsApp/email notification.   

