DOC 05 — Security Design Document
Version 4.0 — Data Protection & DPDP Compliance
1. Layered Defense System
Layer 1: Network Controls: Enforce TLS 1.3 across all communication nodes, route WSS traffic directly to FastAPI to prevent resource exhaustion, and isolate backend databases within private VPC domains.   

Layer 2: Multi-Factor OTP & Sessions: Restrict application entry strictly to OTP validation over mobile, using secure, short-lived RS256 JWT access tokens stored inside httpOnly secure cookies.   

Layer 3: Cryptographic Field Protections: Apply dynamic Fernet AES-256 field-level encryption on PII fields (name, phone, DOB) inside MongoDB. Convert raw Aadhaar numbers into SHA-256 hashes immediately after capture, ensuring raw identifiers are never written to disk.   

Layer 4: Input Validation & Masking: Sanitize incoming prompts to strip out SQL or prompt injections. Run automated masking regex passes to clean sensitive alphanumeric strings (such as PAN cards or Aadhaar formats) before sending transcripts to Gemini.   

Layer 5: DPDP Act 2023 Compliance: Inform citizens about data usage terms via an onboarding screen, capture the exact timestamp of consent, provide comprehensive data erasure options, and process all user info exclusively within domestic cloud regions.   

Layer 6: Audits & Alerts: Automatically record operational actions to write-once, append-only security logs. Configure real-time alerts to notify the team if API error rates spikes above 1%.   

